Hey there Carson fans! It's me! I have great news! Last week someone spoke to foster mom and asked to meet me. I loved them immediately!! They are cat lovers and have a CH kitty like me! They brought me home Thursday night and so far I'm doing great. I fall down more than my new sister who is like me but they will help me learn the house and make adjustments as needed. I'm so excited to start enjoying my new parents! 💜

Thanks to all of you for your love and support since I was surrendered last month. Thanks for sharing my videos and spreading the word about Cerebellar Hypoplasia cats like me! 🐈
Special thanks to my foster parents for taking me in so I was comfortable until I met my furrever parents 💕
Thanks to Willingboro Veterinary Clinic for making me part of the Grand Paws Club even though I insisted I was a young kitten who didn't need bloodwork! 😉
#CatsMeowCarson #cerebellarhypoplasia #rescuecat #specialneedscat #seniorcat #blackcatsrock #spoiledcat #adoptlove

Meet the ever so handsome and charming Smokey! This boy’s happy grin is sure to whisk all your troubles away! He’s not only friendly and connects easily, he loves to show his perfect ‘Sit’ and ‘Shake’! Anything for some head scratches and treats! 😉
Smokey came into the shelter on November 25, 2017 as an Owner Surrender for “Escapes”. It appears they had him his whole life; they reported that Smokey is friendly with children and company. At 9 years old, this lovable guy shouldn’t be sitting in a shelter. Help us to find him a forever home that can keep him safe and secure! Please share, or come meet Smokey today!
💙 Smokey #A1264652 🐾

Meet Ruby, a jolly and vivacious 64 lbs, female who loves spending time with volunteers. Just over 1 year old, she’s still puppy-like and would thrive with an active family who will play with her, teach her and make her a part of the family. This bubbly, lovable sweetheart came to the shelter on Jan 11, 2017 as an OWNER SURRENDER for landlord issues. Her previous owners reported they had Ruby her whole life and she is friendly with children and company. They kept her inside so she is housebroken and the hard kennel floors are extra rough -- she’s used to life in a home. Can you open up your home to this sweet-faced girl and show her the love of a forever family? Please come and meet her! ❣️

Bonni is a well mannered, alert, and gorgeous gal who loves to play fetch! She's extremely sweet, walks well on the leash, and loves to play with her tennis ball in the yard with volunteers. Bonni also fancies herself a lady of leisure and loves to hop up on the chair and sit next to you. She is the perfect mix of a playful dog and couch potato, and is sure to be a loyal companion.
Bonni is a gorgeous 6 years old, spayed female Am Staff mix who came into the shelter on September 13, 2017 having a possible owner. Sadly, no one came forward to claim this great girl.

“Foxy is one of the many #dogs my coworkers and I visit each day in rural parts of North Carolina. While making friends with dogs is a perk, we also do vital things like making sure the dogs have adequate shelter and protection from the elements, clean water, a clean living area, and a hearty meal. We even manage to squeeze in some belly rubs, kisses, and play time with toys! Sometimes we bathe adorable little #puppies! Unwanted litters are surrendered to us and then transferred to a placement partner for the chance at #adoption! We promote spay/neuter at each visit and in many cases, provide transport and surgery free of charge!” – Kate S. #spayandneuter #adopt #adoptlove
